1.download and extract springBootApplication(demo.zip)
2.open demo file in IntelliJ Idea
   -click on load
   -run DemoApplication
3.verify it----http://localhost:8080/api/data
4.Stop the SpringBoot  Application after verification 
5.: Create a repository in Git account and push the code
6.run the commands in terminal
cd ~/Desktop/demo
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/PavithraD62/exp11
if error-------------  git remote remove origin
again execute-----   git remote add origin https://github.com/PavithraD62/exp11
git add .
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

in Github we can see demo file

go to Azure page
1.App services
2.create a resource---->web App
3.(New) sjbit_demo_group1
   give name: sjbit_demo3
4. runtime stack---Java17
5.go to deployment
   select github account
   select organization as-- same github account
   select repository--exp11
   Branch---Main
   down----Enable
6.go to Review+create-----click on create(wait)
7.click--Go to resource
8.copy default domain link and paste it in browser---u will get Java Developers page


open cloud shell
1.run
az ad sp create-for-rbac --name "github-action-deploy" --role contributor \
  --scopes /subscriptions/<your-subscription-id>/resourceGroups/<your-resource-group> \
  --sdk-auth
**replace <your-resource-group> as sjbit_demo_group1   and
                <your-subscription-id> with the subscription id(2f3c4d40-fc97-4e6e-b139-d0bf414bdf56)
2.copy the commands generated

goto github

3.go to secrets and variables-->actions
   create new repository secret
                                    give name AZURE_CREDENTIALS
                                    paste the generated commands inside the secret box
                                    click add secret 
4.go to Github
select Actions on top
create new workflow
configure
delete all the content paste the following

                  yaml file content

change the file name as "main.yml"
click-->commit changes
being getting created---check in details
(extra previous build will also be there---)

Actions---create main.yml(sucessful one)-->click

build and deploy will be sucessfull

in the azure page

refresh view logs---->it will be sucessfull
